Fix: response message and internal data on scan start request

On scan start requests the internal data could get corrupted by updating the status of the scan, but might not be queued.
In addition we now sent a NOT IMPLEMENTED response when starting an stopped or failed scan.

commit.message:
Adjust example config (#1598)

* Add: notus only mode

Introduces modes to control openvasd.

Currently it has the modes:
- service - enables all endpoints and the whole functionality (default)
- service_notus - disables /scan endpoint and nasl feed

The configuration is described within rust/examples/openvasd/config.example.toml
and there is the possibility to set `OPENVASD_MOD` environment variable.

For an example to start openvasd in the notus mode you can it from the
examples dir:

```
FEED_PATH=feed/nasl NOTUS_ADVISORIES=feed/notus/advisories/ OPENVASD_LOG=debug OPENVASD_MODE=service_notus ../target/release/openvasd
```

and try to call `localhost:3000/scans`.

* adjust example config

commit.message:
Add: notus command to nasl-cli

Instead of having a notus main.rs nasl-cli has a subommand notus that
can be used by calling:

```
> echo "man-db-2.6" | target/release/nasl-cli notus -i -p examples/feed/notus/products test
```

Change: hide warning message in standalone mode (#1591)

In standalone mode, there is no host process and IPC context are not initialized.
Sending a message will always fail.

Implement Scanner trait for Openvas scanner (#1585)

* Fix: convertion to openvas port list

* Add: implement FromStr for status phase. Also, take in account the openvas status strings

* Fix: right value for the AliveTestMethods

* Fix: config option name

* Add: host progress to the host_info list. The host progress is necessary for scan progress calculation

* Add: function to get the redis socket path from the openvas configuration

* Fix: start and stop openvas command line options

* Add: relese() kb, get scan_status() and also fix kb_id to return the id of kb and not the id of cache

* Change: add life time to the preference handler and small fixes/chages in preferences

* Changes: make public results struct members and also store the general scan status

* Add: implement start, stop and fetch results traits for openvas scanner

* Release kb on delete

* Add: implement OpenvasPhase.
with this change openvas specific phases are not mixed with the Scanner phases

* Fix: release namespace

* Fix zombie process when scan finished.
Wait the child process if the scan finished and release the kb

commit.message:
Change: Send a message with excluded hosts count to ospd. (#1528)

Also, the excluded hosts count is subtracted from the hosts count sent to ospd.

With this change, openvas sends the information necessary for the progress calculation,
and ospd doesn't have to calculate the excluded hosts and subtract from the total amount of hosts.
